					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>234 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>260</height>
										<width>185</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>220</height>
										<width>120</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>234 folios  (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 3 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>24 quires of 10 leaves each, quires no. 1, 8, 23 and 24 are imperfect.</p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last pages.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several larger lacunae. </p>
									<p>Some leaves are imperfectly preserved.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>Masorah magna occupies one line in the upper and in the lower margin.</p>
									<p>The number of verses and siman are stated at the end of each book.</p>
									<p>Ruled with mastara. </p>
									<p>Catchwords present throughout.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Yemenite square script, punctuated, of 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Zekharyah ben Shelomoh ben Mosheh ha-Leṿi</name>, and <name type="person" role="patron">Avraham ben Zekharyah</name>, inscribed in the colophon, folio 224r. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus n="224r"/> - another contemporary hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 1r: a doodle page.</p>
							<p>Folio 1r, a note of ownership: לקדש כניסת יחיא אלטירי ן' אברהם מן אלנדרים אלדרי בנצר יוסף ן' סאלם אלכרנבא יצ"ו Similar inscription is found on folio 97v.</p>
						</additions>
